The paper deals with the problem of fake news detection, which involves natural language processing and image analysis. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of latent features extracted via multiple convolutional layers suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves feature engineering and information retrieval, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
